<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1758,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,379,1758,1783]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Taxonomic history.</emphasis>
Originally described in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[764,851,1759,1782]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[764,851,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Castnia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it was later placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1210,1300,1759,1782]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hydrobiidae" genus="Geyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1300,1759,1782]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Geyeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Buchecker" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" refString="Buchecker, H. ([1880]) Systema entomologiae sistens insectorum Classe, Genera, Species. Pars 6. Munchen, Author, 2 pp." type="book" year="1880">
Buchecker [
<number box="[158,222,1794,1818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" value="1880.0">1880</number>
]
</bibRefCitation>
). Even though three subspecies were recognized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[819,964,1794,1818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" refString="Miller, J. Y. (1986) The taxonomuy, phylogeny, and zoogeography of the Neotropical Castniinae (Lepidoptera: Castnioidea: Castniidae). Ph. D. Thesis. University of Florida, Gainesville, USA. 571 pp." type="book" year="1986">
Miller (
<number box="[904,964,1794,1818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" value="1986.1995">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[976,1035,1794,1818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" refString="Miller, J. Y. (1995) Castniidae. In: Heppner, J. B. (ed.). Checklist: Part 2. Hyblaeoidea - Pyraloidea - Tortricoidea. Atlas of Neotropical Lepidoptera. Association for Tropical Lepidoptera / Scientific Publications, Gainesville, USA, pp. 133 - 137, 176 - 177." type="book chapter" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
), they were all synonymyzed under 
<taxonomicName box="[151,286,1832,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uruguayana">
<emphasis box="[151,286,1832,1855]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">uruguayana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamas" box="[328,488,1830,1854]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" refString="Lamas, G. (1995) A critical review of J. Y. Miller's Checklist of the Neotropical Castniidae (Lepidoptera). Revista Peruana de Entomologia, 37, 73 - 87." type="journal article" year="1995">
Lamas (
<number box="[418,479,1830,1854]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1758,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,1866,1891]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[697,811,1866,1890]" name="Argentina" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[826,924,1867,1891]" name="Uruguay" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1208,1866,1890]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
where it flies from November through February–March (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[573,711,1902,1926]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" refString="Miller, J. Y. (1986) The taxonomuy, phylogeny, and zoogeography of the Neotropical Castniinae (Lepidoptera: Castnioidea: Castniidae). Ph. D. Thesis. University of Florida, Gainesville, USA. 571 pp." type="book" year="1986">
Miller 
<number box="[651,711,1902,1926]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="56" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1758,2035]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,457,1938,1963]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Biology and behavior.</emphasis>
The flight pattern is slow and hovering, atypical of most 
<taxonomicName box="[1103,1225,1938,1962]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Castniidae</taxonomicName>
. While individuals can be observed flying during mid-day, they occasionally fly at different times if disturbed (
<bibRefCitation author="Miller" box="[1173,1312,1974,1998]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" refString="Miller, J. Y. (1986) The taxonomuy, phylogeny, and zoogeography of the Neotropical Castniinae (Lepidoptera: Castnioidea: Castniidae). Ph. D. Thesis. University of Florida, Gainesville, USA. 571 pp." type="book" year="1986">
Miller 
<number box="[1252,1312,1974,1998]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Biezanko" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" refString="Biezanko, C. M. (1961 a) Castniidae, Zygaenidae, Dalceridae, Eucleidae, Megalopygidae, Cossidae et Hepialidae da Zona Sueste do Rio Grande do Sul. Arquivos de Entomologia, Escola de Agronomia &quot; Eliseu Maciel &quot; (Pelotas) (A), 14, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1961" yearSuffix="a">
Biezanko (
<number box="[159,216,2010,2034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" value="1961.0">1961</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
states that the larvae feed on 
<taxonomicName authority="Cav. &amp; Dombey ex F. Delaroche" authorityName="Cav. &amp; Dombey ex F. Delaroche" box="[570,1199,2010,2035]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Eryngium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paniculatum">
<emphasis box="[570,827,2011,2035]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Eryngium paniculatum</emphasis>
Cav. &amp; Dombey ex F. Delaroche
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1214,1325,2010,2034]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
